  "texts": [
    "Our findings reveal an initial increase in resistance to jailbreaking prompts with moderate pruning (10-30%), followed by a decline in safety when the pruning exceeds a certain threshold.",
    "Notably, the unpruned LLaMA-2 Chat had the most safety training among the three models and showed the highest resilience against jailbreaking prompts.",
    "Post-pruning, the model also showed the most significant safety improvement -an average of 8.5% increase in the refusal rates across five categories.",
    "Conversely, Mistral Instruct v0.2 was the least resilient before pruning and exhibited minimal safety improvement post-pruning.",
    "We also benchmarked the performance of the pruned LLMs across a variety of tasks, including Massive Multitask Language Understanding (MMLU), mathematical reasoning, common sense reasoning, perplexity measurements, and effective context length evaluation."
  ],
